🧩 **Provide a high level summary of OHIF**

* **What OHIF is**

  * An open-source, web-based medical imaging platform for viewing and interacting with DICOM data in the browser

* **Core capabilities**

  * Multi-modality support (CT, MR, PET, SPECT, etc.)
  * 2D/3D visualization (including MIP and volume rendering)
  * Annotation and measurement tools
  * Segmentation support (DICOM SEG, label maps, surfaces)

* **Architecture**

  * Built with **React + TypeScript**
  * Uses **Cornerstone3D** for rendering and image handling
  * Extensible via a **plugin/extension system** (modes, panels, services)

* **Data access**

  * Integrates with **DICOMweb** servers (WADO-RS, QIDO-RS, STOW-RS)
  * Supports cloud backends and custom data sources via adapters

* **Customization & extensibility**

  * Extensions allow adding:

    * Custom tools
    * Workflows (modes)
    * UI components and panels
  * Configurable hanging protocols and viewport layouts

* **Typical use cases**

  * Clinical viewers
  * Research visualization tools
  * AI/ML workflow integration (inference + visualization)

